  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed across blood viscosity, inlet flow rate, and rotational speed boundary conditions using Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000). A screening sensitivity study using one-at-a-time (OAT) perturbations was conducted informally during model development and is referenced in the UQ narrative; however, a ranked list of dominant input drivers has not been encoded as a structured sensitivity analysis record.",
