      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD solver must be under version control with documented release notes and regression test suite.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional license with documented version control. Solver regression tests confirmed against canonical benchmark cases. Achieved level exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver must demonstrate correct implementation of governing equations via manufactured solution or benchmark comparison.",
      "rationale": "Code verification performed against ASME V&V 20 benchmark cases for internal rotating flow. Observed order of accuracy consistent with second-order spatial discretization. No anomalous convergence behavior detected."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be reported for hemolysis index QoI; GCI < 5% required.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse: 2.1M, medium: 5.8M, fine: 14.3M cells). Richardson extrapolation applied; GCI for normalized hemolysis index = 3.1%. Discretization error is within the 5% acceptance threshold."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must match CFD boundary conditions within stated tolerances; flow rate ±3%, speed ±1%.",
      "rationale": "PIV and hemolysis bench tests conducted using FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Flow rate controlled to ±1.5%, rotational speed to ±0.4%. Blood analog (glycerin-water) viscosity characterized at test temperature. Boundary condition correspondence documented in test protocol TP-CPB-2023-04."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., normalized RMS error or validation uncertainty) must be reported for primary QoI.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using validation uncertainty framework per ASME V&V 20. Comparison error E = 8.3% for hemolysis index; validation uncertainty Uval = 11.7%. E < Uval, indicating model is not invalidated. Velocity field NRMS error 4.2% at primary operating point. Achieved level 3 reflects multi-QoI quantitative comparison with uncertainty bounds."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation must be the same or directly traceable to the QoIs used in the clinical decision.",
      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) used as both validation metric and decision criterion. Hemolysis model (power-law, Giersiepen coefficients) applied consistently in validation and prediction contexts. QoI relevance confirmed by clinical consultant review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must cover the operating envelope (flow rate 3–7 LPM, speed 2000–3500 RPM) relevant to CPB use.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments span 5 operating points within the CPB operating envelope (3 LPM/2000 RPM through 7 LPM/3500 RPM). Pump geometry identical to prediction geometry. Blood analog properties matched to clinical blood viscosity range. Validation activities are assessed as directly relevant to the COU."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated to residual levels below 1e-5 for all transport equations.",
      "rationale": "Not assessed as a separate factor at MRL 2; convergence monitoring is embedded within the discretization error study. Residual histories reviewed informally and confirmed stable convergence, but formal factor assessment is scoped to MRL 3 and above for this device class."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs and boundary conditions must be reviewed by a second analyst.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2 for Class II devices with medium model influence. Peer review of simulation setup was performed informally as part of team QA practice but is not counted toward a formal factor assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis sub-model selection must be justified relative to available literature benchmarks.",
      "rationale": "Model form assessment deferred at MRL 2; the k-omega SST turbulence model and power-law hemolysis model were selected based on published literature for similar pump geometries. Formal model form factor assessment is not required at the current risk level."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters must be documented with sources and nominal values; material properties must be traceable to measurement or literature.",
      "rationale": "Blood density (1060 kg/m3), dynamic viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s at 37°C), and pump geometry dimensions documented with traceability to manufacturer drawings and ASTM F1841 standard. Boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, outlet pressure, rotational speed) specified per clinical operating range. Uncertainty in input parameters was propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (N=2000 Latin hypercube draws) covering ±10% viscosity, ±5% flow rate, and ±2% rotational speed. The UQ narrative references an informal OAT screening sensitivity study performed during model development that suggested viscosity was the dominant driver of hemolysis index variability; however, this screening was not formalized into a ranked sensitivity analysis and no structured hasSensitivityAnalysis record was generated."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Number of experimental replicates must be sufficient to characterize measurement variability.",
      "rationale": "Test sample assessment not required at MRL 2 for this COU. Three experimental replicates were performed at each operating point as standard laboratory practice, but formal statistical characterization of inter-sample variability is not required until MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Differences between validation experiment inputs and clinical use inputs must be documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters not formally assessed at MRL 2. Blood analog (glycerin-water, 36% by mass) used in bench tests differs from clinical blood; the viscosity match at 37°C is within 8% of physiological blood viscosity. This difference is acknowledged in the UQ narrative but has not been propagated through a formal equivalency assessment."
    }
  ],
